message:
revert(e2e): restore explicit match arms in validate_benchmark_metadata_records

Intentional partial revert of the earlier clippy cleanup in this
same batch ("style(e2e): clippy cleanup pass on benchmark/honesty/
persistent phase + visibility tweak") that collapsed the
BenchmarkComparisonMode match into guarded arms with a `_ => {}`
catch-all.

Restoring the explicit-arm form:

    Some(BenchmarkComparisonMode::Parity) => {
        if csqlite.dimensions != frankensqlite.dimensions { push }
    }
    Some(BenchmarkComparisonMode::Control) => {
        if csqlite.dimensions == frankensqlite.dimensions { push }
    }
    None => {}

preserves exhaustiveness over BenchmarkComparisonMode so the
compiler will force us to update this function whenever a new
comparison mode variant is added.  The earlier `_ => {}` form
would silently swallow any new variant and fail to enforce the
intended "every variant must have an explicit policy" invariant.

Add a targeted
    #[allow(clippy::collapsible_match)]
above the outer match so the lint doesn't force a re-collapse,
and an inline comment spelling out why:

    // Explicit arms (no `_ => {}` catch-all) preserve exhaustiveness
    // so future additions to BenchmarkComparisonMode force updates here.

Clippy is right that the guarded-arm form is shorter; it's wrong
that the shorter form is a strict improvement here.  Exhaustiveness
is the contract, and it's worth the extra nesting to keep.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

